CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper May 25, 1957, pg. 28, reads: "Little Leaguers - One of the teams in the Little League of Penn Township, is the "Tigers,' who play in the midget division. Shown above, from left to right, front row: Dennis O'Connell, Frank Weisser, William Hawkins, Thomas Williams, Joseph Carmach, Thomas Perry. Second row: Robert McKeag, Raymond McKeag, Russell Sinclair, Glenn Malone, Curtis Robertson, Albert Ross, Raymond Porter. In rear: Coaches William O'Connell, Frank Summers, manager, Gerald Reardon. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Tigers Little League Baseball team members, first row from left: Group Dennis O'Connell, Frank Weisser, William Hawkins, Thomas Williams, Joseph Carmach, Thomas Perry; second row: Robert McKeag, Raymond McKeag, Russell Sinclair, Glenn Malone, Curtis Robertson, Albert Ross, Raymond Porter; rear: coaches William O'Connell, manager Frank Summers, and coach Gerald Reardon posed in front of chain link fence on foggy or smoky day
